article.headline: Oral Roberts 75, McNeese St. 54
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Shawn Glover had 24 points, Damen Bell-Holter added 22 and Oral Roberts dominated inside with a 75-54 victory over McNeese State on Saturday night. Oral Roberts (12-8, 7-1 Southland) outscored the Cowboys 44-22 inside the paint, shot 54.4 percent from the field and out-rebounded McNeese State 41-28. Glover and Bell-Holter each added eight rebounds to their scoring totals. Korey Billbury scored eight points, dished out eight assists and had six rebounds for Oral Roberts. The Golden Eagles built a 34-23 lead at halftime and never looked back. Oral Roberts led by as many as 22 in the second half. Kevin Hardy was the only McNeese State (8-10, 2-6) player in double figures with 12 points while recording six assists and four rebounds. The Cowboys shot only 38.1 percent from the field and was 5 for 20 from beyond the arc. Oral Roberts has won four straight and seven of its last eight games.
